  "text": "The final message is that abnormal findings on nailfold capillaroscopy at baseline together with a systemic sclerosisspecific autoantibody indicate a very high probability of developing definite systemic sclerosis whereas their absence excludes this outcome [CITATION_1] . In SSc patients awareness of this sequence of microvascular damage and SS-associated autoantibodies has potential implications for future therapeutical trials.",
